:"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Order/Archimedean/Class.html#FiniteMulArchimedeanClass.mk\"><span class=\"name\">FiniteMulArchimedeanClass</span>.<span class=\"name\">mk</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">M</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Defs.html#CommGroup\">CommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Defs/LinearOrder.html#LinearOrder\">LinearOrder</a> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Order/Monoid/Defs.html#IsOrderedMonoid\">IsOrderedMonoid</a> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">a</span> : <span class=\"fn\">M</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h</span> : <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Ne\">≠</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Order/Archimedean/Class.html#FiniteMulArchimedeanClass\">FiniteMulArchimedeanClass</a> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Create a `FiniteMulArchimedeanClass` from a non-one element. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/Order/Archimedean/Class.html#FiniteMulArchimedeanClass.mk","kind":"def","line":718,"name":"FiniteMulArchimedeanClass.mk","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Algebra/Order/Archimedean/Class.lean#L718-L721"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Order/Archimedean/Class.html#FiniteArchimedeanClass\"><span class=\"name\">FiniteArchimedeanClass</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">M</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Defs.html#AddCommGroup\">AddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Defs/LinearOrder.html#LinearOrder\">LinearOrder</a> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Order/Monoid/Defs.html#IsOrderedAddMonoid\">IsOrderedAddMonoid</a> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1</div></div>","info":{"doc":"`FiniteArchimedeanClass M` is the quotient of the non-zero elements of the additive group `M` by\nadditive archimedean equivalence, where two elements `a` and `b` are in the same class iff\n`(∃ m : ℕ, |b| ≤ m • |a|) ∧ (∃ n : ℕ, |a| ≤ n • |b|)`.\n\nIt is defined as the subtype of non-top elements of `ArchimedeanClass M`\n(`⊤ : ArchimedeanClass M` is the archimedean class of `0`).\n\nThis is useful since the family of non-top archimedean classes is linearly independent. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/Order/Archimedean/Class.html#FiniteArchimedeanClass","kind":"def","line":705,"name":"FiniteArchimedeanClass","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Algebra/Order/Archimedean/Class.lean#L705-L713"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Order/Archimedean/Class.html#FiniteMulArchimedeanClass\"><span class=\"name\">FiniteMulArchimedeanClass</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">M</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Defs.html#CommGroup\">CommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Defs/LinearOrder.html#LinearOrder\">LinearOrder</a> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Order/Monoid/Defs.html#IsOrderedMonoid\">IsOrderedMonoid</a> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1</div></div>","info":{"doc":"`FiniteMulArchimedeanClass M` is the quotient of the non-one elements of the group `M` by\nmultiplicative archimedean equivalence, where two elements `a` and `b` are in the same class iff\n`(∃ m : ℕ, |b|ₘ ≤ |a|ₘ ^ m) ∧ (∃ n : ℕ, |a|ₘ ≤ |b|ₘ ^ n)`.\n\nIt is defined as the subtype of non-top elements of `MulArchimedeanClass M`\n(`⊤ : MulArchimedeanClass M` is the archimedean class of `1`).\n\nThis is useful since the family of non-top archimedean classes is linearly independent. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/Order/Archimedean/Class.html#FiniteMulArchimedeanClass","kind":"def","line":697,"name":"FiniteMulArchimedeanClass","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Algebra/Order/Archimedean/Class.lean#L697-L714"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Order/Archimedean/Class.html#ArchimedeanClass.ballAddSubgroup_antitone\"><span class=\"name\">ArchimedeanClass</span>.<span class=\"name\">ballAddSubgroup_antitone</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">M</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Defs.html#AddCommGroup\">AddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Defs/LinearOrder.html#LinearOrder\">LinearOrder</a> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Order/Monoid/Defs.html#IsOrderedAddMonoid\">IsOrderedAddMonoid</a> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Monotone/Defs.html#Antitone\">Antitone</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Order/Archimedean/Class.html#ArchimedeanClass.ballAddSubgroup\">ballAddSubgroup</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/Order/Archimedean/Class.html#ArchimedeanClass.ballAddSubgroup_antitone","kind":"theorem","line":689,"name":"ArchimedeanClass.ballAddSubgroup_antitone","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Algeb